The main event at Turffontein on Saturday is named after Senor Santa, who raced in the 1980s and 1990s in the colours of Fred and Harold Cawdry and was trained in KwaZulu-Natal by Tony Rivalland and Willie Pieters. This weekendâ€™s race is a 1160m straight dash and has attracted a decent entry of tough speedsters, with tightly grouped betting odds telling of the competitiveness. A record of seven Grade 1 victories at distances from 1000m to 1600m attests to the legend Senor Santa. He competed and won from age two to eight, amassing 15 victories and two Champion Sprinter titles...